          <selectionEntries>
            <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Magna-grapple" hidden="false" id="54ce-9ee1-cd6c-a048">
              <costs>
                <cost name="Points" typeId="6f18-a8fc-2c5b-9517" value="15"/>
              </costs>
              <profiles>
                <profile name="Magna-grapple" typeId="8e6f-7553-28c5-95a0" typeName="Weapons" hidden="false" id="1473-6105-eeb8-4024">
                  <characteristics>
                    <characteristic name="Range" typeId="9b9e-0c24-e409-a801">12&quot;</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="Str." typeId="1ebc-896c-43de-904a">8</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="AP" typeId="730c-47dc-fdad-3c8b">2</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="Type" typeId="1524-30c8-5da7-66ff">Heavy 1</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="45fd-0f50-e1d0-907c">If the Magna-grapple shot hits a vehicle and the target is not destroyed, roll a D6 and add 8 to the score. If the result is lover than the target&apos;s highest armour value, nothing happens. If the result is equal to or higher than the target&apos;s highest armour value, move the vehicle 2D6&quot; directly towards the Dreadnought.


The target does not change facing and will stop if it comes within 1&quot; or difficult terrain, impassable terrain, another vehicle (friend or foe) or a unit locked in close combat. Teat any non-vehicle unit the target moves over as having been tank-shocked. After the attack, the target will be able to move normally in it&apos;s next turn.</characteristic>
                  </characteristics>
                </profile>
              </profiles>
              <constraints>
                <constraint type="max" value="1" field="selections" scope="parent" shared="true" id="0f7e-5a45-80e8-5db9" includeChildSelections="false"/>
              </constraints>
            </selectionEntry>
